choices.text:
just jet-lag. Most adult/teenagers in Russia “wake up at 10/11”; sleep moderately-decently; work (if employed); then sleep at 1am.

As a contrast, in my family, my parents “wake up at sunrise (i.e. 6-8am), go to work (commute for 1.5/3h), then eat at 8/9, and carpool back home at 5/6 (late dinner at 7ish).” Then sleep 11pm. Rest of the fam sleeps odd/late hours.

I never adjusted to that strict schedule. (Not that I tried, but why go against family culture)

The bug downtime, which is when Russians both sleep and work. (My family is non-tech, if very savvy - my dad just upgraded his os. Not sure that counts as nerdy.)

But the only thing that mattered  
Was just being a fly. If I could just fly,  
I would make a lucky, lucky catch,  
And victory would be in the bag.

The life of a fly. The hardest life of them all.

But alas, I wasted my prime years, feeling sorry  
For myself, exclaiming words of why.  
``Why me? Why? ``  
Out loud, sometimes, just out loud.

So as I age, my bad eyesight  
Keeps me grounded, poor menial me  
On the ground.

As I age
